        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "To track down bugs in remote XML-RPC methods, I frequently run into the need to debug the request and response with the client and I found the current method (using lastResponse) rather not good.\n\nI pretty much took PEAR's approach here - while it may be a bit radical for some, but echo'ing values straight really does the debug trick. The patch is for Zend\/XmlRpc\/Client.php. And this is more or less a proposal. ;-) If you give me feedback and ideas, I'll refine it.\n\nhttp:\/\/www.lagged.de\/oss\/zend\/Client.patch.gz"
        },
