            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13379",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assigning to Matthew to review the patch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-15T13:53:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-15T13:53:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13432",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I didn't include it in this patch, but I'd also propose a public method, \"setDebug\" in order to enable\/disable debugging on the fly without passing it to the constructor. \n\n{code:title=setDebug|borderStyle=solid}\npublic function setDebug($debug)\n{\n  if (is_boolean($debug) === false)\n  {\n    return false;\n  }\n  $this->_debug = $debug;\n  return $debug;\n}\n{code} ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-16T10:07:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-16T10:07:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14501",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Matthew:\n\nOn the mailing list I saw you recommended turning on extensive error logging on the remote system to debug calls and response, however there's circumstances where you a) have no access to the server-part or b) it maybe not written in PHP (and beyond the scope).\n\nSo I'd really like to get this patch\/feature included, since it aids development.\n\nLet me know your thoughts.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-07T12:04:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-07T12:04:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14656",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can accomplish this debugging yourself using the client as is, with a couple of different methods. \n\nIn the first method, you do all logging after the request has been made:\n{code}\n$proxy = $client->setProxy();\n$proxy->user->add($data);\n\n$httpClient = $client->getHttpClient();\necho $httpClient->getLastRequest();\necho $httpClient->getLastResponse()->asString();\n{code}\nThe above will print the entire HTTP request and response strings from the XML-RPC request you last made.\n\nIn the second method, you would override the HTTP client adapter you use, overriding the write() method such that you capture and echo the request to the screen, and the read() method such that you echo the response to the screen prior to returning it:\n{code}\nclass My_Http_Client_Adapter extends Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Socket\n{\n    public function write($method, $uri, $http_ver = '1.1', $headers = array(), $body = '')\n    {\n        $request = parent::write($method, $uri, $http_ver, $headers);\n        echo '<pre>', $request, '<\/pre>';\n        return $request;\n    }\n\n    public function read()\n    {\n        $response = parent::read();\n        echo '<pre>', $response, '<\/pre>';\n        return $response;\n    }\n}\n{code}\n\nYou would register this with the xml-rpc client's HTTP client via:\n{code}\n$client->getHttpClient()->setAdapter(new My_Http_Client_Adapter());\n{code}\nprior to making any actual xml-rpc requests.\n\nI personally don't like echoing the debug calls straight to the screen; when I've used PEAR's client, this sort of debugging is very intrusive, and tends to wreak havoc with your output. Zend_XmlRpc_Client and Zend_Http_Client provide plenty of mechanisms to enable it, however  -- as well as more robust mechanisms via Zend_Log -- so I see no need to add it by default to the class.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-17T14:08:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-17T14:08:37.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
